text: Gabrielle Louis-Carabin (born February 20, 1946 in Le Moule, Guadeloupe) was a member of the National Assembly of France, representing Guadeloupe's 2nd constituency from 2002 to 2017 as a member of the Union for a Popular Movement. ==References== * page on the French National Assembly website ' Category:1946 births Category:Living people Category:People from Le Moule Category:Guadeloupean politicians Category:Union for a Popular Movement politicians Category:Deputies of the 12th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 14th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Women members of the National Assembly (France) Category:21st-century French women politicians Category:Black French politicians
title: Gabrielle Louis-Carabin
